main event: A civilian reported observing four round, disk-type objects in the sky for about 20 minutes in Chicago on September 15, 1966.
interesting points: The objects were about 13 inches in diameter and white-gray in color., The sighting was initially observed from a seventh-floor window., The objects were observed in a trail formation, approximately 50 feet apart., The observer used binoculars to observe the objects., The objects faded out after being visible for about 30 seconds.
